The workers were trapped in the tunnel.

10
00:00:26,886 --> 00:00:29,012
With no way out.

11
00:00:29,012 --> 00:00:33,310
The collapsed wall of stones and mud 
standing between them and their way out,

12
00:00:33,310 --> 00:00:35,186
was 60 meters long.

13
00:00:35,186 --> 00:00:40,492
Soon, a concerned group of people 
gathered in this small city in Uttarakhand.

14
00:00:40,492 --> 00:00:42,360
The next day, on November 13th,

15
00:00:42,360 --> 00:00:44,331
the rescue mission began officially,

16
00:00:44,331 --> 00:00:46,981
involving over 200 individuals.

17
00:00:46,981 --> 00:00:50,453
It took 17 days of intensive efforts to 
successfully extricate the trapped workers.

18
00:00:50,453 --> 00:00:52,065
How did they achieve this feat?

19
00:00:52,065 --> 00:00:55,982
Let's understand the entire rescue operation 
in today's video, with 3D animations.

20
00:00:55,982 --> 00:00:58,729
Furthermore, let's answer the biggest question.

21
00:00:58,729 --> 00:01:00,621
What is the underlying cause of the incident?

22
00:01:00,621 --> 00:01:03,829
The root cause is the same that is faced by Joshimath,

23
00:01:03,829 --> 00:01:08,526
a situation often overlooked 
by mainstream news channels.

24
00:01:08,526 --> 00:01:09,648
Let's begin.

25
00:01:18,231 --> 00:01:21,673
The incident unfolded in Uttarkashi district in Uttarakhand,

26
00:01:21,673 --> 00:01:23,824
specifically in the Barkot-Silkyara tunnel,

27
00:01:23,824 --> 00:01:26,295
this map shows its location.

28
00:01:26,295 --> 00:01:28,888
This is a two-lane bi-directional tunnel

29
00:01:28,888 --> 00:01:34,244
being constructed as a part of the Modi 
Government's ₹120 billion Char Dham project.

30
00:01:34,244 --> 00:01:36,774
Let's talk about the details of the project later in the video,

31
00:01:36,774 --> 00:01:38,574
but broadly speaking,

32
00:01:38,574 --> 00:01:41,934
this is a highway project connecting 4 North Indian Dhams.

33
00:01:41,934 --> 00:01:45,431
Badrinath, Kedarnath, 
Yamunotri, and Gangotri.

34
00:01:45,431 --> 00:01:48,149
Roads will be built connecting these four dhams,

35
00:01:48,149 --> 00:01:49,921
to reduce the travelling distance between them.

36
00:01:49,921 --> 00:01:54,437
PM Modi laid the foundation stone 
of this project in December 2016.

37
00:01:54,437 --> 00:01:58,235
This particular tunnel was announced in February 2018.

38
00:01:58,235 --> 00:02:02,126
under the Brahmakhal-Yamunotri National Highway section.

39
00:02:02,126 --> 00:02:06,257
The purpose of this tunnel was to reduce 
the distance between Gangotri and Yamnotri

40
00:02:06,257 --> 00:02:08,323
by approximately 20 km and 
45 minutes of travel time.

41
00:02:08,323 --> 00:02:12,933
The estimated cost of the project is ₹13.83 billion,

42
00:02:12,933 --> 00:02:16,533
overseen by Navyug Engineering Company Limited

43
00:02:16,533 --> 00:02:17,563
under the guidance of

44
00:02:17,563 --> 00:02:20,816
the National Highways and Infrastructure Development Corporation Limited.

45
00:02:20,816 --> 00:02:25,634
From the Silkyara side, 2,340 meters 
of construction was nearly over.

46
00:02:25,634 --> 00:02:28,885
And from Barkot, 1,600 meters was constructed. 

47
00:02:28,885 --> 00:02:34,221
The collapsed tunnel section was situated 
270 meters from the Silkyara entrance,

48
00:02:34,221 --> 00:02:37,957
the debris from the collapse formed a 60 meters thick wall.

49
00:02:37,957 --> 00:02:42,296
Fortunately, since 2,000 meters of the tunnel was already constructed,

50
00:02:42,296 --> 00:02:44,350
the trapped labourers

51
00:02:44,350 --> 00:02:47,754
had a space of 2,000 meters to stretch their legs.

52
00:02:47,754 --> 00:02:51,721
Fortunately, they weren't trapped in a small space.

53
00:02:51,721 --> 00:02:55,567
The height of the enclosure they were trapped in was 8.5 meters.

54
00:02:55,567 --> 00:02:57,728
Typically, incidents of this nature are

55
00:02:57,728 --> 00:02:59,314
classified as "Act of God,"

56
00:02:59,314 --> 00:03:01,328
signifying that it was a natural disaster.

57
00:03:01,328 --> 00:03:05,839
However, the degree to which these events are 
influenced by natural and human factors

58
00:03:05,839 --> 00:03:07,768
is a subject of ongoing discussion.

59
00:03:07,768 --> 00:03:09,722
As per the government's press release,

60
00:03:09,722 --> 00:03:12,333
the workers were engaged in reprofiling work,

61
00:03:12,333 --> 00:03:15,230
a process involving adjustments to the tunnel structure.

62
00:03:15,230 --> 00:03:17,038
This activity becomes necessary when

63
00:03:17,038 --> 00:03:21,811
the surrounding rocks exhibit unexpected 
behaviours that went unnoticed previously.

64
00:03:21,811 --> 00:03:25,925
The exact cause of the collapse will 
remains unknown until further research.

65
00:03:25,925 --> 00:03:28,021
However, preliminary findings suggest

66
00:03:28,021 --> 00:03:31,921
this collapse was due to a potential geological fault

67
00:03:31,921 --> 00:03:33,933
known as the Shear Zone.

68
00:03:33,933 --> 00:03:37,992
This refers to a thinner or weaker part of the Earth's crust,

69
00:03:37,992 --> 00:03:41,550
The construction would have put 
a strain on the surrounding rocks,

70
00:03:41,550 --> 00:03:44,038
leading to a landslide.

71
00:03:44,038 --> 00:03:47,913
Another consideration as stated by 
ML Sharma, a professor from IIT Roorkee,

72
00:03:47,913 --> 00:03:51,041
is the presence of undetected cavities in the rocks,

73
00:03:51,041 --> 00:03:54,054
gaps between these mountain rocks.

74
00:03:54,054 --> 00:03:57,641
These cavities naturally weaken such areas, 

75
00:03:57,641 --> 00:03:59,700
increasing the risk of landslides.

76
00:03:59,700 --> 00:04:01,367
These are 2 possible causes,

77
00:04:01,367 --> 00:04:02,688
but we can only speculate right now

78
00:04:02,688 --> 00:04:06,125
and the definitive reason will be established 
only after the completion of investigation reports.

79
00:04:06,125 --> 00:04:09,905
There are two main approaches to constructing 
a tunnel construction in mountainous terrain,

80
00:04:09,905 --> 00:04:12,455
the first is the drill and blast method (DBM),

81
00:04:12,455 --> 00:04:16,481
and the second is by using a tunnel boring machine (TBM).

82
00:04:16,481 --> 00:04:20,550
The former involves drilling holes in stones,

83
00:04:20,550 --> 00:04:23,353
placing explosives,

84
00:04:23,353 --> 00:04:25,743
and literally blasting the rocks.

85
00:04:25,743 --> 00:04:29,286
It's as if a small bomb is detonated from inside the rocks.

86
00:04:29,286 --> 00:04:31,760
It is the simple and traditional approach.

87
00:04:31,760 --> 00:04:34,770
Using the tunnel boring machine is a more expensive

88
00:04:34,770 --> 00:04:36,607
but safer alternative.

89
00:04:36,607 --> 00:04:40,605
The machine creates a hole in the rocks with a rotating head,

90
00:04:40,605 --> 00:04:44,643
and precast concrete segments are then installed.

91
00:04:44,643 --> 00:04:48,548
Unfortunately, in the Himalayan mountains, 
we cannot use these machines.

92
00:04:48,548 --> 00:04:51,551
Due to the extreme geological conditions.

93
00:04:51,551 --> 00:04:52,964
As you have studied in school,

94
00:04:52,964 --> 00:04:56,049
the Himalayas are the youngest mountain ranges in the world.

95
00:04:56,049 --> 00:04:58,499
At only 40-50 million years old,

96
00:04:58,499 --> 00:05:00,320
they continue to grow,

97
00:05:00,320 --> 00:05:04,560
resulting in highly sensitive 
and unpredictable conditions.

98
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:08,809
Consequently, accidents in these areas 
resulting from extensive construction

99
00:05:08,809 --> 00:05:11,829
cannot be solely attributed to 'Act of God.'

100
00:05:11,829 --> 00:05:17,380
Nevertheless, even in challenging situations, 
people often seek a divine explanation.

101
00:05:17,380 --> 00:05:18,821
Consider this article,

102
00:05:18,821 --> 00:05:22,868
where a local resident claims that there 
was a Baba Baukh Nath's temple on the site

103
00:05:22,868 --> 00:05:26,135
which was removed to make way 
for the highway construction. 

104
00:05:26,135 --> 00:05:27,865
He claims that this was the cause of the incident.

105
00:05:27,865 --> 00:05:31,320
Attempts to find a divine cause behind 
natural or man-made disasters

106
00:05:31,320 --> 00:05:33,014
are not unprecedented.

107
00:05:33,014 --> 00:05:35,654
In the case of the 2013 Kedarnath floods,

108
00:05:35,654 --> 00:05:41,481
some locals attributed the calamity to 
the relocation of Dhari Devi's shrine

109
00:05:41,481 --> 00:05:44,283
during the construction of 
the Alaknanda Hydroelectric Project.

110
00:05:44,283 --> 00:05:49,726
During the rescue efforts in the tunnel, 
where over 200 people were involved,

111
00:05:49,726 --> 00:05:54,926
a small temple was constructed at the 
entrance of the tunnel on November 18th,

112
00:05:54,926 --> 00:05:56,141
and rituals were conducted.

113
00:05:56,141 --> 00:05:57,933
Interestingly, this initiative wasn't 
undertaken by the locals

114
00:05:57,933 --> 00:05:59,869
but by NHIDCL,

115
00:05:59,869 --> 00:06:04,025
the same company overseeing the tunnel construction.

116
00:06:04,025 --> 00:06:06,570
However, neither the temple

117
00:06:06,570 --> 00:06:08,762
nor the subsequent rescue operation 
would have been needed

118
00:06:08,762 --> 00:06:12,521
had an emergency escape passage 
been incorporated as per the original plan.

119
00:06:12,521 --> 00:06:15,165
When the Government sanctioned this project,

120
00:06:15,165 --> 00:06:18,534
they had clearly stipulated the necessity of an escape passage,

121
00:06:18,534 --> 00:06:21,564
a way out in case of emergency was mandatory. 

122
00:06:21,564 --> 00:06:23,013
as per government guidelines,

123
00:06:23,013 --> 00:06:24,467
such emergency exits

124
00:06:24,467 --> 00:06:28,770
are recommended for every tunnel 
exceeding 1.5 km in length.

125
00:06:28,770 --> 00:06:32,209
PC Nawani, the former director of the 
Geological Survey of India, emphasizes that

126
00:06:32,209 --> 00:06:36,278
managing projects of this nature 
without escape routes is impractical.

127
00:06:36,278 --> 00:06:38,914
The entire incident could have been 
averted had proper precautions been taken.

128
00:06:38,914 --> 00:06:41,787
But anyhow, let's get back to the incident,

129
00:06:41,787 --> 00:06:44,506
the truth was, the workers were trapped indeed.

130
00:06:44,506 --> 00:06:45,803
How could they be rescued?

131
00:06:45,803 --> 00:06:48,452
This marked the beginning of "Operation Zindagi"
[Operation Life]

132
00:06:48,452 --> 00:06:52,732
Uttarakhand government formed a five-option rescue plan

133
00:06:52,732 --> 00:06:56,585
to be carried out by five distinct agencies:

134
00:06:56,585 --> 00:06:59,810
Oil and Natural Gas Corporation (ONGC),

135
00:06:59,810 --> 00:07:02,968
Satluj Jal Vidyut Nigam (SJVNL),

136
00:07:02,968 --> 00:07:05,437
Rail Vikas Nigam Ltd (RVNL),

137
00:07:05,437 --> 00:07:10,128
National Highways and Infrastructure Development Corporation Ltd (NHIDCL),

138
00:07:10,128 --> 00:07:13,069
and Tehri Hydro Development Corporation (THDCL).

139
00:07:13,069 --> 00:07:15,527
Additionally, the Border Roads Organisation (BRO)

140
00:07:15,527 --> 00:07:18,711
and the National Disaster Response Force (NDRF)

141
00:07:18,711 --> 00:07:20,951
stood ready on the sidelines,

142
00:07:20,951 --> 00:07:23,925
offering assistance whenever required.

143
00:07:23,925 --> 00:07:26,245
The first step in the rescue operation focused on

144
00:07:26,245 --> 00:07:29,041
ensuring a continuous oxygen supply to the trapped individuals

145
00:07:29,041 --> 00:07:30,877
so that they could breathe properly.

146
00:07:30,877 --> 00:07:35,769
A compressed air pipe was manoeuvred 
between the debris for this.

147
00:07:35,769 --> 00:07:39,857
Simultaneously, a separate 4-inch pipe was passed through the debris

148
00:07:39,857 --> 00:07:43,347
to deliver snacks and dry fruits.

149
00:07:43,347 --> 00:07:46,496
These measures were implemented 
on the first day, November 12th.

150
00:07:46,496 --> 00:07:49,074
Notably, electricity was being supplied in the tunnel,

151
00:07:49,074 --> 00:07:52,711
