00:12:41,167 --> 00:12:44,054
The workers received their first hot meal since they were trapped,

251
00:12:44,054 --> 00:12:45,900
a serving of hot khichdi.

252
00:12:45,900 --> 00:12:52,148
An endoscopic camera was passed 
through the pipe to film the workers,

253
00:12:52,148 --> 00:12:55,494
This was the first video where we could see them.

254
00:13:06,435 --> 00:13:12,578
Beyond food, the pipe became a conduit for medicines, 
mobile phones, chargers, and walkie-talkies,

255
00:13:12,578 --> 00:13:16,202
The walkie-talkies enabled direct 
communication with the workers.

256
00:13:16,202 --> 00:13:19,693
On the same day, it was decided to dig two additional tunnels

257
00:13:19,693 --> 00:13:21,794
to create additional escape routes.

258
00:13:21,794 --> 00:13:23,763
By 21st November,

259
00:13:23,763 --> 00:13:28,546
four 900 mm pipes had been 
successfully inserted through the debris.

260
00:13:28,546 --> 00:13:31,641
However, the rescue operation was 
still far from being successful,

261
00:13:31,641 --> 00:13:35,603
with the pipes interfering with the drilling.

262
00:13:35,603 --> 00:13:39,299
This interference led to a slight delay on November 22.

263
00:13:39,299 --> 00:13:41,318
Further setbacks occurred on November 23

264
00:13:41,318 --> 00:13:43,625
when the platform upon which 
the drilling machine was placed,

265
00:13:43,625 --> 00:13:44,988
had weakened,

266
00:13:44,988 --> 00:13:47,688
that night was spent repairing that structure.

267
00:13:47,688 --> 00:13:51,751
By November 24, the drilling machine had to be reassembled,

268
00:13:51,751 --> 00:13:54,121
and the sequence of challenges persisted.

269
00:13:54,121 --> 00:13:57,450
Once something was set right 
something other broke down.

270
00:13:57,450 --> 00:14:00,731
On November 25, a significant setback unfolded

271
00:14:00,731 --> 00:14:03,656
as the auger machine completely broke down

272
00:14:03,656 --> 00:14:05,749
and was lodged in the tunnel.

273
00:14:05,749 --> 00:14:07,752
Arnold Dix informed reporters that

274
00:14:07,752 --> 00:14:10,885
the drilling machine had already broken 
down thrice during the rescue operations

275
00:14:10,885 --> 00:14:13,188
and was now completely destroyed.

276
00:14:13,188 --> 00:14:14,504
"The Auger is broken.

277
00:14:14,504 --> 00:14:16,023
-Broken?
-Yeah, broken.

278
00:14:17,469 --> 00:14:19,161
Yeah, the machine is busted.

279
00:14:19,161 --> 00:14:20,347
It's irreparable.

280
00:14:20,347 --> 00:14:21,333
It is destructed.

281
00:14:21,333 --> 00:14:22,969
No more work from Auger."

282
00:14:22,969 --> 00:14:25,045
On November 26, authorities announced

283
00:14:25,045 --> 00:14:27,703
their intention to attempt vertical drilling again.

284
00:14:27,703 --> 00:14:32,102
By then, 20 meters had been drilled vertically,

285
00:14:32,102 --> 00:14:34,899
but the primary focus remained on horizontal drilling,

286
00:14:34,899 --> 00:14:37,728
with only 12 meters of drilling left.

287
00:14:37,728 --> 00:14:40,542
Recognizing the machine's irreparable state, 
on November 27, a decision was made

288
00:14:40,542 --> 00:14:43,502
to resort to manual drilling,

289
00:14:43,502 --> 00:14:46,000
by bringing in rat hole miners.

290
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:50,088
Rat hole mining, an old and 
hazardous coal extraction method,

291
00:14:50,088 --> 00:14:52,121
was used in the past.

292
00:14:52,121 --> 00:14:54,669
It involved creating vertical passages by hand.

293
00:14:54,669 --> 00:14:59,501
The passage would be barely big 
enough for a person to pass through it.

294
00:14:59,501 --> 00:15:03,001
Despite being banned in India by the National Green Tribunal,

295
00:15:03,001 --> 00:15:05,911
due to its adverse environmental impact

296
00:15:05,911 --> 00:15:08,174
and the unsafe conditions for the miners,

297
00:15:08,174 --> 00:15:11,991
in this situation, it was deemed the 
best option for this rescue operation.

298
00:15:11,991 --> 00:15:15,134
A team of 12 rat hole mining experts worked diligently,

299
00:15:15,134 --> 00:15:17,967
and by the evening of November 28,

300
00:15:17,967 --> 00:15:21,350
it was reported that only 2 meters of digging remained.

301
00:15:21,350 --> 00:15:23,608
Everyone waited for the good news with bated breaths,

302
00:15:23,608 --> 00:15:25,546
and finally, around 8 in the evening

303
00:15:25,546 --> 00:15:28,585
the first worker was successfully 
brought out on a stretcher.

304
00:15:28,585 --> 00:15:35,452
Subsequently, one by one, all 41 workers 
were rescued from this tunnel.

305
00:15:35,452 --> 00:15:38,903
"After 17 days of being trapped in 
the collapsed tunnel in Northern India,

306
00:15:38,903 --> 00:15:41,775
rescuers have now freed all 41 workers."

307
00:15:41,775 --> 00:15:44,644
Munna Qureshi was one of these 12 rat-hole mining expert,

308
00:15:44,644 --> 00:15:47,464
he said that it was an emotional moment.

309
00:15:47,464 --> 00:15:50,342
He was the one who removed the last piece of debris.

310
00:15:50,342 --> 00:15:53,219
He could see them once he removed the last piece.

311
00:15:53,219 --> 00:15:55,822
He said that those workers hugged them

312
00:15:55,822 --> 00:15:58,333
and thanked them once they were safely outside.

313
00:15:58,333 --> 00:16:01,386
They worked incessantly for 24 hours to rescue the workers.

314
00:16:01,386 --> 00:16:03,701
Qureshi said that his happiness knew no bounds,

315
00:16:03,701 --> 00:16:05,493
and that he did it for his country.

316
00:16:05,493 --> 00:16:08,360
Ambulances and helicopters stood ready outside,

317
00:16:08,360 --> 00:16:10,692
the rescued workers were adorned with garlands,

318
00:16:10,692 --> 00:16:14,630
and a freshly cooked meal awaited them.

319
00:16:14,630 --> 00:16:17,410
Potatoes and cauliflower stew, roti, lentil soup, and rice

320
00:16:17,410 --> 00:16:19,676
were served to them as they emerged.

321
00:16:19,676 --> 00:16:24,191
The entire nation celebrated the safe rescue of these 41 workers,

322
00:16:24,191 --> 00:16:26,162
and praises poured in for the rescuers.

323
00:16:26,162 --> 00:16:30,641
However, amidst the celebration for 
this happy ending, it is crucial not to forget

324
00:16:30,641 --> 00:16:33,027
the underlying cause of the incident

325
00:16:33,027 --> 00:16:36,462
and the need to address its root cause.

326
00:16:36,462 --> 00:16:39,538
Waiting for an official investigation may not be necessary,

327
00:16:39,538 --> 00:16:43,468
as the actual reasons behind the incident are already known.

328
00:16:43,468 --> 00:16:45,098
The answer to the question lies within

329
00:16:45,098 --> 00:16:47,403
the Char Dham Highway project,

330
00:16:47,403 --> 00:16:50,687
The same reason that is contributing 
to the sinking of Joshimath.

331
00:16:50,687 --> 00:16:55,412
This so-called development in Uttarakhand,

332
00:16:55,412 --> 00:16:58,769
exemplified by projects like Char Dham,
adversely impacting the environment, 

333
00:16:58,769 --> 00:17:02,852
escalating the risk of landslides and related accidents.

334
00:17:02,852 --> 00:17:04,781
I am not making this up,
look at this article

335
00:17:04,781 --> 00:17:08,481
"Tunnel collapse in Uttarakhand is a part 
of a bigger problem in the Himalayas" 

336
00:17:08,481 --> 00:17:11,692
In the construction of roads, there was inadequate slope analysis.

337
00:17:11,692 --> 00:17:15,152
There is extreme slope cutting at some places,

338
00:17:15,152 --> 00:17:19,320
slopes have been cut up to 45 degrees to construct the roads.

339
00:17:19,320 --> 00:17:22,170
This can cause landslides easily.

340
00:17:22,170 --> 00:17:27,410
In fact, the region has witnessed an average 
of one landslide per day over the past 2 years.

341
00:17:27,410 --> 00:17:28,762
According to this article.

342
00:17:28,762 --> 00:17:33,955
Environmental activists have 
raised concerns about this project.

343
00:17:33,955 --> 00:17:35,732
In February 2018,

344
00:17:35,732 --> 00:17:38,542
Citizens for Green Doon, an NGO based in Dehradun,

345
00:17:38,542 --> 00:17:41,017
lodged a complaint with the National Green Tribunal (NGT),

346
00:17:41,017 --> 00:17:45,535
highlighting the catastrophic impact of 
this project on the Himalayan ecology.

347
00:17:45,535 --> 00:17:50,122
They pointed out that, at that time, 25,000 trees 
had already been felled for the project,

348
00:17:50,122 --> 00:17:52,288
violating the Forest Conservation Act.

349
00:17:52,288 --> 00:17:53,889
Furthermore, the NGO emphasized that,

350
00:17:53,889 --> 00:17:55,523
according to Indian environmental laws,

351
00:17:55,523 --> 00:17:58,632
every highway project exceeding 100 km

352
00:17:58,632 --> 00:18:02,315
requires an environmental impact assessment.

353
00:18:02,315 --> 00:18:05,897
However, the government 
unabashedly circumvented this regulation

354
00:18:05,897 --> 00:18:10,074
they said that this wasn't a mega project 
of thousands of kilometers of highways,

355
00:18:10,074 --> 00:18:13,057
they claimed to undertake 53 smaller projects,

356
00:18:13,057 --> 00:18:15,648
each highway with a length of 
less than 100 kilometers.

357
00:18:15,648 --> 00:18:19,553
This mega project was presented as a cluster of small projects

358
00:18:19,553 --> 00:18:21,221
simply to bypass this law.

359
00:18:21,221 --> 00:18:23,983
Consequently, in September 2018, the NGT ruled that

360
00:18:23,983 --> 00:18:26,600
the project did not need an environmental clearance.

361
00:18:26,600 --> 00:18:31,209
This order was later contested in the 
Supreme Court of India in August 2019,

362
00:18:31,209 --> 00:18:35,368
leading to the appointment of a 
26-member High-Powered Committee,

363
00:18:35,368 --> 00:18:38,847
led by environmentalist Ravi Chopra.

364
00:18:38,847 --> 00:18:43,314
The committee had to investigate the potential 
environmental and social ramifications

365
00:18:43,314 --> 00:18:45,275
of this project in Uttarakhand

366
00:18:45,275 --> 00:18:47,013
and provide recommendations based on their findings.

367
00:18:47,013 --> 00:18:51,045
In July 2020, the 4 members of this committee, including Ravi Chopra,

368
00:18:51,045 --> 00:18:54,083
took note of the government's guidelines from March 2018,

369
00:18:54,083 --> 00:18:56,744
issued by the Ministry of Road and Transport Highways.

370
00:18:56,744 --> 00:18:59,461
These guidelines specified that highways constructed on mountains

371
00:18:59,461 --> 00:19:02,641
should not exceed a total width of 7 meters.

372
00:19:02,641 --> 00:19:06,355
However, the government aimed for 
12-meters-wide highways on these mountains.

373
00:19:06,355 --> 00:19:10,373
The other 21 committee members 
supported the government's plan.

374
00:19:10,373 --> 00:19:14,873
In response, Ravi Chopra directly wrote to 
the Environment Ministry in August 2020, 

375
00:19:14,873 --> 00:19:18,412
expressing concern beyond tree felling.

376
00:19:18,412 --> 00:19:22,200
He emphasized that, in addition to cutting down trees and mountains,

377
00:19:22,200 --> 00:19:24,920
the waste generated during road construction

378
00:19:24,920 --> 00:19:27,520
was being indiscriminately dumped into rivers,

379
00:19:27,520 --> 00:19:30,044
particularly in eco-sensitive zones

380
00:19:30,044 --> 00:19:31,839
such as Kedarnath Wildlife Sanctuary,

381
00:19:31,839 --> 00:19:33,423
Valley of Flowers National Park,

382
00:19:33,423 --> 00:19:34,722
and Rajaji National Park.

383
00:19:34,722 --> 00:19:37,004
Waste was being dumped at such places.

384
00:19:37,004 --> 00:19:38,630
The following month, in September 2020,

385
00:19:38,630 --> 00:19:41,507
the Supreme Court considered 
Ravi Chopra's recommendation

386
00:19:41,507 --> 00:19:46,799
and ruled that the highway's width 
should not exceed 7 meters.

387
00:19:46,799 --> 00:19:48,072
This made sense as

388
00:19:48,072 --> 00:19:50,082
wider roads would necessitate

389
00:19:50,082 --> 00:19:53,833
more slope cutting, tree removal,

390
00:19:53,833 --> 00:19:55,923
and more waste being dumped,

391
00:19:55,923 --> 00:19:59,054
which could destabilise the Himalayan terrain

392
00:19:59,054 --> 00:20:02,631
and increase the chances of 
landslides and flash floods.

393
00:20:02,631 --> 00:20:05,613
"We observed unanimously 

394
00:20:05,613 --> 00:20:08,873
that the road width was the key factor 

395
00:20:08,873 --> 00:20:11,817
which determines the extent of hill-cutting 

396
00:20:11,817 --> 00:20:14,342
and the subsequent environmental damage."

397
00:20:14,342 --> 00:20:17,577
However, instead of adhering to the Supreme Court's decision, the government

398
00:20:17,577 --> 00:20:20,560
employed a new masterstroke

399
00:20:20,560 --> 00:20:23,000
to circumvent the Supreme Court's direction.

400
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:26,320
In November 2020, the Ministry of Defence entered the scene,

401
00:20:26,320 --> 00:20:28,635
appealing to the Supreme Court for

402
00:20:28,635 --> 00:20:31,094
the construction of a double-lane road,

403
00:20:31,094 --> 00:20:33,120
citing it as a necessity for the Army.

404
00:20:33,120 --> 00:20:35,603
The Char Dham project was reframed,

405
00:20:35,603 --> 00:20:38,413
asserting that it was essential for 
the country's benefit and the Army.

406
00:20:38,413 --> 00:20:40,577
That's why the roads had to be so wide.

407
00:20:40,577 --> 00:20:42,205
While the public had been initially informed

408
00:20:42,205 --> 00:20:47,290
that the road construction was for the 
Char Dham Yatra and religious pilgrimage,

409
00:20:47,290 --> 00:20:50,370
the project's purpose was suddenly recast

410
00:20:50,370 --> 00:20:51,927
as a strategic imperative.

411
00:20:51,927 --> 00:20:53,787
Rooted in national interest,

412
00:20:53,787 --> 00:20:58,229
specifically facilitating the movement 
of Indian troops to the Chinese border.

413
00:20:58,229 --> 00:20:59,904
The new reason was that since China

414
00:20:59,904 --> 00:21:01,832
was constructing roads on its side of the border,

415
00:21:01,832 --> 00:21:03,432
India needed to do the same.

416
00:21:03,432 --> 00:21:05,795
However, a major difference is the terrain.

417
00:21:05,795 --> 00:21:08,847
China's territory lies on the Tibetan Plateau,

418
00:21:08,847 --> 00:21:11,862
characterized by fewer mountains,

419
00:21:11,862 --> 00:21:13,620
a relatively stable landscape,

420
00:21:13,620 --> 00:21:14,757
building roads is easier there

421
00:21:14,757 --> 00:21:17,919
with fewer adverse ecological impacts.

422
00:21:17,919 --> 00:21:20,370
Following this appeal by the Ministry of Defence,

423
00:21:20,370 --> 00:21:23,956
the Ministry of Highways modified its 
2018 directives the subsequent month,

424
00:21:23,956 --> 00:21:26,120
stating that the 7-meter guideline

425
00:21:26,120 --> 00:21:27,945
could be expanded to 10 meters

426
00:21:27,945 --> 00:21:31,340
if a project holds strategic importance.

427
00:21:31,340 --> 00:21:34,338
A year later, on December 14, 2021,

428
00:21:34,338 --> 00:21:37,587
the Supreme Court reluctantly approved

429
00:21:37,587 --> 00:21:41,634
the continuation of the Char Dham project as it is.

430
00:21:41,634 --> 00:21:46,931
Consequently, the highways in the 
Char Dham project are 12 meters wide.

431
00:21:46,931 --> 00:21:49,761
Looking at how unabashedly the government

432
00:21:49,761 --> 00:21:52,905
has disregarded rules and guidelines for this project,

433
00:21:52,905 --> 00:21:56,265
Ravi Chopra resigned from the committee.

434
00:21:56,265 --> 00:22:02,010
As of today, the Char Dham project has 
resulted in the clearance of 600 hectares of forest,

435
00:22:02,010 --> 00:22:04,826
the felling of over 56,000 trees,

436
00:22:04,826 --> 00:22:08,938
and the widening of 75% of the Char Dham highway.

437
00:22:08,938 --> 00:22:14,972
The Ministry of Highways acknowledged 
200 landslides in the area in 2021,

438
00:22:14,972 --> 00:22:18,984
And in November 2021, they admitted to the Supreme Court that

439
00:22:18,984 --> 00:22:24,000
125 landslides were triggered around 
the route of the Char Dham project

440
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:25,997
attributed to the construction work.

